While researching cybercrime, I found UPI fraud to be one of the most common and impactful threats, especially among students and young users. I was surprised to learn how easily people can be tricked into authorizing payments by simply entering their UPI PIN under false assumptions.
One important realization for me was that many users do not clearly understand that entering a UPI PIN always means sending money, not receiving it. This misunderstanding is often exploited by attackers.
As a result of this task, I will be more cautious while handling online transactions. I will always verify payment requests, avoid clicking on unknown links, and never share sensitive information like OTPs or PINs. This task helped me understand the importance of digital awareness in preventing cybercrime.
